{
  "stem": "1917.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 329.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would be marched there, put in a huge room, maybe 10 sets of twins at a time in one room with about 5 or 6 doctors all dressed in white coats.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would keep us naked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would measure every part of our body, compare it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Let's say, put an instrument and squeeze it against our skull to see the size of the head; then compare it to child's; then compare it between each set of twins-- the nose, the ears, the eyes, the shape of the face.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On occasion, they would photograph everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Other times, they would paint us with something that was like a dark-- some kind of a paint.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then they would wipe it up and wash it off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were-- these experiments, for all its practical purposes, were not deadly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they were extremely difficult to deal with-- six to eight hours being naked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't think that anybody, even us in Auschwitz, wanted to feel like a piece of meat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we have been reduced, in this case, to a mass of breathing, living cells.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So much of the detail of the experiment I still do not remember, because the only way I could cope with it is by blocking it out.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would let my mind just take off into other directions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I know from some of the twins, and from the testimony from the mock trial that I organized in Jerusalem, in 1985, that Mengele would take twins in reproductive age, which would be teenagers-- 12, 13, 14, 15-- and castrate some of the boys.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have heard of one testimony.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, he-- and I talked to one of the twins myself, a 16-- she was a 16-year-old girl-- and did cross transfusion between boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
